up against a black <add>gold</add> stormy sunset got a touch of majesty<lb/>
&amp; vulnerability (?) which they had never possessed before.  It was<lb/>
the passing thought of the moment and tomorrow in all<lb/>
its stark ghostliness I have not doubt I shall fail to <lb/>
see it.  Sometimes I have thought I should like to bring<lb/>
you to visit my many resting places here but on the<lb/>
whole I think not no matter under what 'aspect' this<lb/>
place can ever have any attraction for me</p>

<p>No mail has come today owing to the boat not<lb/>
going, either mines or submarines I suppose I expect I<lb/>
shall get some quite undeserved p r communications later! especially<lb/>
if it does not run tomorrow.  This will I expect often be<lb/>
the case this winter but I hope it not often be on<lb/>
<del>Sat</del> Fridays as you will then miss 2 mails running with<lb/>
the Sunday post.</p>

<p>Have written a brief line to young Edward</p>

<opener><salute>Your b w </salute>

<signed> W B Spender </signed></opener>

<p>We tried again to placate the Powers &amp; were again unsuccessful<lb/>
so will have another attempt <del>wasteful</del> but it really is rather<lb/>
unnecessary toil.</p>
        
    

    
         
