            <date>To be posted 28 <del>July</del> <add>Oct</add></date>

<salute>My p r</salute><lb/>

<p>The weather has changed tonight &amp; is dry for once but<lb/>
I doubt if it lasts and anyhow the roads will be a long 6<lb/>
months I expect before they get rid of their <unclear>shine</unclear>, unless<lb/>
we get frost.  The <unclear>salvisan</unclear> has arrived at least 10 days<lb/>
before it became necessary.  Many thanks.</p>

<p>There was a bit of a rumpus.  The Army which<lb/>
I'm afraid likes to get at our Corps began to complain and<lb/>
naturally the blame falls on the only division.  I was not<lb/>
at all sure the b w would not be the scapegoat but I<lb/>
believe the G rather stuck up for me.  Anyhow for the moment<lb/>
in am in <add>the</add> Black books because of an unsuccessful little<lb/>
raid which in present circumstances I described as <del>Comp</del> Tomfoolery<lb/>
both to Gen' G and to a youngster of the Army Staff<lb/>
who was sent down to get a report.  I was really put <lb/>
out and asked him to tell his G people what I thought.</p>

<p>A b w on his hind paws is not a very dangerous <lb/>
animal &#x2014; much more so when standing on his head as<lb/>
the p r knows! so I don't expect much will come of it.<lb/>
However I hope the Corps will soon get other youngsters to<lb/>
to play with.  It is rather like being the only boy at a<lb/>
a big school with the full teaching staff.</p>

